I"0<h3 id="pre-requisites">Pre-requisites</h3>
<p>You need to be familiar with using QGIS.
You need to have QGIS 3.16 installed.<br />
<!-- Additionally, install the Qgis2threejs plugin --></p>

<h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>
<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Download all the .py files and copy to the QGIS Processing Scripts folder.  You can check the location of the Scripts folder as follows:</p>

    <p>QGIS &gt;Setings &gt;Options &gt;Processing &gt;Scripts</p>

    <p>If the folder does not exist, create it by typing in your desired folder.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create and save a new QGIS Project.  Download and copy qsettings and all its files into the project folder.  You can check the location of the project folder as follows:
 QGIS &gt;Project &gt;Properties &gt;Variables &gt;Project &gt;project_folder</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Optional: click on the + button at the bottom right and add a new variable project_font_size.  Type in your desired size - for example, 8, or 14 et cetera.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Download and copy samples and all its files into the project folder.  Drag and drop the files into QGIS.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="using-the-quantumipmptools">Using the QuantumIPMPTools</h3>
<ol>
  <li>The Quantum IPMP Tools are available from:
 QGIS &gt; Processing &gt;Toolbox &gt;Scripts</li>
</ol>

